1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,533
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,533 --> 00:00:02,800
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:05,066 --> 00:00:06,066
What?

4
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:08,333
I'm talking about that five-year-old girl
who you abandoned...

5
00:00:08,333 --> 00:00:10,400
and don't even remember,
who might as well not exist.

6
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:13,733
Were you that disappointed
when she found her way home after all?

7
00:00:16,700 --> 00:00:18,200
You should've abandoned me again.

8
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:20,600
You should've made sure
I could never find my way home again!

9
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:24,200
Honey.

10
00:00:28,633 --> 00:00:30,933
What did you just say?

11
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:35,533
I should've abandoned you again?
Abandon you?

12
00:00:35,633 --> 00:00:36,633
Honey, please.

13
00:00:36,933 --> 00:00:38,433
Please stop!

14
00:00:39,300 --> 00:00:40,400
I was five years old.

15
00:00:41,100 --> 00:00:42,733
It was when I broke your powder compact.

16
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:45,300
That day, you scolded me harshly
and left the house.

17
00:00:46,100 --> 00:00:49,100
I followed you to the playground
by the construction site.

18
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:57,500
The playground by the construction site?

19
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,000
You said,

20
00:01:02,533 --> 00:01:03,800
"Wait here."

21
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:06,733
"Mom will come back for you soon."

22
00:01:08,633 --> 00:01:09,800
Wait here.

23
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:14,900
Mom will come back for you soon.

24
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:16,400
Honey, are you okay?

25
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,033
But you never came.

26
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:22,900
The sun went down,
and everything turned dark.

27
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,000
No matter how long I waited,
you never came in the end.

28
00:01:32,933 --> 00:01:35,100
Why did you make that promise
if you weren't coming?

29
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:38,433
You should've just said
you were abandoning me.

30
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,000
That I shouldn't wait.

31
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,833
If you had just told me the truth
like that...

32
00:01:42,233 --> 00:01:43,233
Stop it, Eun Ae!

33
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:47,300
Eun Nim, take your sister upstairs. Hurry.

34
00:01:48,300 --> 00:01:49,433
Honey, let's go inside.

35
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:54,300
Eun Ae, let's go upstairs, okay?

36
00:02:05,233 --> 00:02:07,600
Honey, lie down for now, okay?

37
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,900
Honey, what do I do?

38
00:02:14,733 --> 00:02:16,600
I really must have abandoned Eun Ae.

39
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:20,233
That day, I went there
when I wasn't in my right mind.

40
00:02:20,233 --> 00:02:22,233
But Eun Ae followed me all the way there.

41
00:02:24,533 --> 00:02:28,433
How could I have completely forgotten that
until now?

42
00:02:36,833 --> 00:02:39,300
Where are we, Mom?

43
00:02:42,533 --> 00:02:45,233
Eun Ae, wait here.

44
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:47,933
Mom will come back for you soon.

45
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:50,800
No, I want to come with you.

46
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,500
I said I'll be right back.

47
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:55,500
Don't go anywhere. Wait right here, okay?

48
00:02:57,133 --> 00:02:58,200
Mom.

49
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:11,333
It was definitely somewhere around here.

50
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:13,700
That restaurant.

51
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:20,333
Yeon Sun!

52
00:03:21,233 --> 00:03:22,800
Where did you go, Yeon Sun?

53
00:03:23,133 --> 00:03:24,133
Mom?

54
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,933
Mom!

55
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:29,600
- Mom!
- Yeon Sun.

56
00:03:30,433 --> 00:03:31,433
Yeon Sun.

57
00:03:34,133 --> 00:03:35,133
What is it?

58
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:40,500
I mistook you for someone else.

59
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:41,900
I'm sorry.

60
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:44,600
Mom.

61
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:48,000
Kim Yeon Sun, where were you?

62
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,200
I looked everywhere for you.

63
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:51,700
Let's go.

64
00:04:09,633 --> 00:04:11,033
I had completely forgotten...

65
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,433
that I went there with Eun Ae that day,

66
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,233
that I left her there like that.

67
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:24,200
Eun Ae must have felt it that day too.

68
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:29,000
The same fear and sadness...

69
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:33,500
that I felt.

70
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:39,500
Eun Ae must have been in so much pain
all this time.

71
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:45,633
I didn't know
something like that had happened either.

72
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:49,300
Do you...

73
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:52,800
know what saying I hate the most?

74
00:04:54,533 --> 00:04:56,533
That a daughter takes after
her mother's fate.

75
00:04:57,433 --> 00:04:59,600
I was afraid my daughter
might take after my fate.

76
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:03,900
That's why I was even more overbearing.

77
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:08,100
I wanted to raise my children well,
without the wounds I had,

78
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:10,800
without any shadows over them.

79
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:15,100
And yet, in the end...

80
00:05:17,633 --> 00:05:20,333
Honey, let's just tell them everything.

81
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:21,900
Let's tell them
why you did that back then...

82
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:24,533
and what that place means to you.

83
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:28,400
I really didn't want
to pass my shadow down to my children.

84
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:35,033
I was so afraid my shadow
would spread to them too.

85
00:05:37,833 --> 00:05:39,100
That's why I couldn't tell them.

86
00:05:42,533 --> 00:05:44,033
What have I done?

87
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:48,200
What have I done to Eun Ae?

88
00:05:54,200 --> 00:06:00,400
<i>On the way to Mom's work</i>

89
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:05,600
<i>White wild rose</i>

90
00:06:07,733 --> 00:06:14,133
<i>The white petals of the wild rose</i>

91
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:19,100
<i>Taste good too</i>

92
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:20,100
Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

93
00:06:22,433 --> 00:06:23,533
Team Manager.

94
00:06:24,733 --> 00:06:27,300
It really is you.
Why are you here at this hour?

95
00:06:28,133 --> 00:06:29,533
What about you, Team Manager?

96
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:32,100
Me? I'm here to inspect the site.

97
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:34,300
Well, I come here often anyway.

98
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,200
What brings you here, Ms. Cho?

99
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:41,300
This is my hideout.
I've come here often since I was little.

100
00:06:42,233 --> 00:06:45,733
Your hideout? Did you live
in this neighborhood as a child?

101
00:06:45,733 --> 00:06:46,733
No.

102
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:50,500
It's not like this playground is only
for people who live in this neighborhood.

103
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,800
Did you cry? What's wrong with your face?

104
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:56,700
What do you mean?

105
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:03,600
You seem to have so many different faces.

106
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,400
What?

107
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:09,000
Sometimes, you're so bright
that it's impossible to handle.

108
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:12,233
Sometimes,
you're so reckless it's almost scary.

109
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:13,900
And sometimes,

110
00:07:14,533 --> 00:07:17,800
like today, you look like you're carrying
all the weight of the world alone.

111
00:07:20,733 --> 00:07:22,633
Which face is the real you?

112
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:29,400
I didn't know I had that many faces.

113
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:33,100
Must be nice for you, Team Manager.

114
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:36,700
Your face never shows
what you're thinking.

115
00:07:37,433 --> 00:07:38,800
That makes it easy to hide.

116
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:41,400
Are you saying I'm wearing a mask?

117
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:42,933
A mask might be too much.

118
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:48,233
Then again, you probably don't have
any emotions to hide from others.

119
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:51,400
There's no way you have any wounds
that other people don't know about.

120
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:54,833
Why do you think that?

121
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:58,600
I saw your award speech
dedicated to your grandfather.

122
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:02,100
You were born as the grandson
of someone like the Chairman.

123
00:08:02,533 --> 00:08:05,533
You're talented enough
to win a world-class award too.

124
00:08:06,233 --> 00:08:08,733
And when people compete
to become successors,

125
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:12,100
usually there's some kind of feud
between siblings.

126
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:14,300
But the CPO and you...

127
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:16,033
don't have that either.

128
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:19,633
You grew up with a silver spoon...

129
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:22,700
in a perfect family full of love.

130
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:25,300
What kind of wound
could you possibly have?

131
00:08:26,633 --> 00:08:30,433
Have you ever heard
that what you see isn't everything?

132
00:08:32,033 --> 00:08:34,400
Why? Are you saying...

133
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:36,833
you have some invisible wound?

134
00:08:37,133 --> 00:08:38,600
Maybe I do.

135
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:41,200
Even you, who seem to never care
about what others think...

136
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:43,500
and don't seem afraid
of anything in the world,

137
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:46,533
have moments where you crouch down
and cry like this.

138
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:55,500
Dad, where is Bit Na?

139
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:58,600
She's sleeping with Mom
in the master bedroom.

140
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:02,033
Mom must be very upset because of me.

141
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:09,600
Did you cry because of me?

142
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:13,233
I told you not to worry too much.

143
00:09:13,933 --> 00:09:17,600
More importantly,
I heard Ji Seon asked you for a divorce.

144
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,200
Did you hear that from Bit Na?

145
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:24,900
What are you two going to do?
What's this about a divorce?

146
00:09:25,133 --> 00:09:27,800
We have Bit Na. That will never happen.

147
00:09:28,733 --> 00:09:29,733
That's right, honey.

148
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:32,633
Ji Seon probably just said it once
out of anger.

149
00:09:32,933 --> 00:09:35,900
How could divorce be that easy
for parents with a child?

150
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:37,500
He's right.

151
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:40,433
Ji Seon may seem a little cold
on the outside,

152
00:09:40,933 --> 00:09:43,000
but she cares so much about Bit Na and me.

153
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,700
And I'll return the money
Eun Ae sent soon too.

154
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:49,700
What are you saying?
Eun Ae sent you the money?

155
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:58,833
My goodness, I didn't even know that.

156
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:02,200
Mom, did you say something to Eun Ae?

157
00:10:05,233 --> 00:10:08,500
Honey, call Eun Ae and ask where she is.

158
00:10:14,100 --> 00:10:15,600
Did you think about what I said earlier?

159
00:10:16,100 --> 00:10:17,100
What did you say?

160
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:20,500
That for those six months,
I shouldn't think about anything else...

161
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:21,900
and just work hard?

162
00:10:23,033 --> 00:10:25,400
That depends on you, Team Manager.

163
00:10:26,100 --> 00:10:28,233
I might do it
if you make me truly want to work...

164
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,200
from the bottom of your heart.

165
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:33,000
I guess this won't do.

166
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,800
We'll have to write another contract.

167
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,100
What? Another contract?

168
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,633
A contract saying that for six months,
you won't think about anything else...

169
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:43,500
and will cooperate
on this retirement community project.

170
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:46,400
If you sign that,
I'll open the server for you.

171
00:10:46,933 --> 00:10:49,800
You mean it?
You'll open the server for me?

172
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:52,533
Should we write that contract right now?

173
00:10:52,533 --> 00:10:54,100
I knew it.

174
00:10:54,100 --> 00:10:55,633
You're too obsessed with the server.

175
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,900
How can I possibly trust you?

176
00:10:57,900 --> 00:11:00,800
Hey, there's an old saying,

177
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,000
"If you trust, blessings will come."

178
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:04,000
Isn't it,
"If you smile, blessings will come?"

179
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:35,400
I'm sorry, Eun Ae.

180
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:40,700
I'm so sorry.

181
00:11:49,733 --> 00:11:51,000
Got you.

182
00:11:51,333 --> 00:11:53,433
You even have Ms. Cho's photo open
on your monitor.

183
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:11,900
What are you doing over there?

184
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:16,200
Don't tell me...

185
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:19,133
you were checking...

186
00:12:19,133 --> 00:12:21,200
if Ms. Cho Eun Ae's photo
was on Gyeol's monitor.

187
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:23,100
Chief Ko.

188
00:12:23,433 --> 00:12:25,000
Jealousy doesn't suit you.

189
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:27,300
What are you talking about?

190
00:12:27,533 --> 00:12:29,700
Someone as confident and wonderful
as you being jealous?

191
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:31,700
That's something people like me do.

192
00:12:33,633 --> 00:12:34,633
Let's go.

193
00:12:35,633 --> 00:12:36,633
Where?

194
00:12:36,733 --> 00:12:39,200
A site visit. Let's work outside too.

195
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,300
You said we were going on a site visit.

196
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:47,800
Is this the site visit location
you were talking about?

197
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,033
We need to warm up before that.

198
00:12:50,033 --> 00:12:52,533
Where are we going
that we need to warm up first?

199
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:55,300
To focus on work,
you need to clear your head.

200
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:57,700
But right now, your head is full
of all kinds of distracting thoughts.

201
00:12:58,200 --> 00:13:00,300
Can you really work properly like that?

202
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:03,200
Here, take it.

203
00:13:09,333 --> 00:13:10,500
Here we go.

204
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:37,500
Why are you making gimbap?

205
00:13:38,633 --> 00:13:40,633
I don't like burdock root or carrots.

206
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:43,000
Your sister likes them.

207
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:48,000
I always left out burdock root and carrots
because of you and Eun Hyeong.

208
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:50,500
Are you trying to make up with Eun Ae?

209
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:52,333
But Mom,

210
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:55,800
what did she mean yesterday
when she said you abandoned her?

211
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:58,400
Your sister just misunderstood a little...

212
00:14:00,833 --> 00:14:04,100
No, I made a huge mistake.

213
00:14:05,233 --> 00:14:08,300
What could have happened between you two
that I don't know about?

214
00:14:09,300 --> 00:14:11,600
Please give us a warm and happy ending.

215
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:13,700
- I'm off.
- Take this with you.

216
00:14:14,233 --> 00:14:15,900
I left out the burdock root and carrots.

217
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:17,433
I don't think I'll need lunch.

218
00:14:17,900 --> 00:14:20,000
Why not? Aren't you going to the library?

219
00:14:20,933 --> 00:14:22,833
Of course I am. I'm off.

220
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:26,400
I told you I didn't put burdock root
or carrots in your lunch.

221
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:33,333
How come I never once made gimbap
that Eun Ae likes?

222
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:40,500
Welcome.

223
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:45,800
Surely I won't run into
that perverted psycho again today, right?

224
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:53,700
I wonder what Napkin Genius is like.

225
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,600
Why is that crazy girl here again?

226
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,100
Stay at home and rest.

227
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:07,600
I really need to stop coming to this cafe.

228
00:15:09,233 --> 00:15:10,500
This just won't do.

229
00:15:14,900 --> 00:15:16,933
I'm sure I'll recognize them
at first sight.

230
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:18,600
My soulmate.

231
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,533
Who could Oh My Oz be?

232
00:15:30,833 --> 00:15:31,833
Excuse me.

233
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:33,600
Are you Oh My Oz?

234
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,000
What?

235
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:39,300
What is it?

236
00:15:40,300 --> 00:15:42,000
You are, right? My soulmate.

237
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,533
Nice to meet you. I'm the Napkin...

238
00:15:44,533 --> 00:15:45,800
What are you talking about?

239
00:15:48,300 --> 00:15:51,033
What? You're...

240
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,300
Napkin Genius?

241
00:15:55,433 --> 00:15:58,333
No way, Oh My Oz...

242
00:15:59,133 --> 00:16:00,200
My Oz...

243
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:02,133
Oh My Oz.

244
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:03,700
- You again?
- You again?

245
00:16:14,033 --> 00:16:15,033
I'm coming in.

246
00:16:28,133 --> 00:16:29,133
Get up.

247
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:33,833
I made gimbap.

248
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:38,033
I added lots of burdock root and carrots,
just the way you like it.

249
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:43,633
I'm sorry.

250
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:47,300
I'm sorry I slapped you.

251
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:51,300
And I'm sorry for giving you a hard time
because of Eun Hyeong's money problem.

252
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:58,200
I really had completely forgotten
about that day.

253
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:02,000
That day, there was...

254
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:04,733
something that made me do that.

255
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,400
There was something?

256
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:10,833
What could possibly make
a mother forget her own child?

257
00:17:10,833 --> 00:17:11,833
Does that even make sense?

258
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:16,033
There is something. I can't tell you now.

259
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:24,100
But really, it was nothing like that.

260
00:17:25,233 --> 00:17:27,100
Why would I ever abandon you?

261
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,300
You're my child,
more precious than my own body.

262
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:32,133
Do you really not know your mom that well?

263
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:36,933
I was lacking in so many ways.

264
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:39,600
I was only full of greed,

265
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:43,100
always pushing you kids too hard.

266
00:17:45,733 --> 00:17:47,500
And since you eat everything so well,

267
00:17:48,333 --> 00:17:51,100
I always adjusted the food
for your picky brother and Eun Nim.

268
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:55,033
I never even made
your favorite burdock and carrot gimbap.

269
00:17:57,800 --> 00:17:58,800
I just...

270
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:02,433
never properly learned how to be a mother.

271
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:10,000
I'm sorry. I mean it.

272
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,000
Hey.

273
00:18:22,633 --> 00:18:24,800
My daughter is really angry at me.

274
00:18:26,133 --> 00:18:28,433
What should I do to make her forgive me?

275
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:33,600
Why aren't you answering?
Can't you hear me?

276
00:18:35,100 --> 00:18:36,233
Her name is Joy.

277
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:39,200
You're trying to talk to her
without even knowing her name?

278
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:41,200
Joy?

279
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:45,000
She didn't answer
because I didn't call her by her name?

280
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:48,800
Joy.

281
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:52,400
Yes, I am Joy. How can I help you?

282
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:55,300
She answers when I call her name.

283
00:18:57,233 --> 00:19:00,700
Joy, my daughter is mad at me,

284
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:04,500
and now she won't even eat
her favorite burdock and carrot gimbap.

285
00:19:04,733 --> 00:19:06,000
What should I do?

286
00:19:06,300 --> 00:19:08,200
Hunger wins over everything,

287
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:10,233
so if you starve her for a few days,
she'll eat it.

288
00:19:10,733 --> 00:19:13,833
What? She's so silly.

289
00:19:14,100 --> 00:19:16,400
Mom, stop bothering Joy.

290
00:19:16,533 --> 00:19:18,300
I'll eat it.

291
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:23,633
Did you really put in
a lot of burdock root and carrots?

292
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:25,633
Of course I did.

293
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:38,400
So pretty.

294
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:01,000
Stop taking pictures, Gyeol.

295
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:02,900
I'm so embarrassed I could die.

296
00:20:03,900 --> 00:20:06,933
I'm done. Now enjoy your time together.

297
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:09,133
I'll check into the hotel
and put your luggage upstairs.

298
00:20:09,133 --> 00:20:10,500
I'll come pick you up in about two hours.

299
00:20:10,533 --> 00:20:12,433
All right, good work.

300
00:20:12,433 --> 00:20:13,433
Don't mention it.

301
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,200
Well then, let's go.

302
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:19,200
Why are you holding my hand
like young people do?

303
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:22,400
Today, let's go back
to being 20-year-old Lee Yeong Hwa...

304
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:25,133
and 30-year-old Ko Kang Su.

305
00:20:26,433 --> 00:20:28,233
It feels like it was just yesterday.

306
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:31,600
How beautiful.

307
00:20:33,633 --> 00:20:34,833
Isn't it beautiful?

308
00:20:36,100 --> 00:20:38,600
To me, you're even more beautiful.

309
00:20:39,933 --> 00:20:42,600
From the first time I saw you
at the construction site...

310
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:45,000
until today, always.

311
00:20:57,533 --> 00:20:59,500
- You've worked hard.
- You've worked hard.

312
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:00,500
You've worked hard.

313
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:02,433
Once that side is finished,
I think we'll be done.

314
00:21:02,433 --> 00:21:04,000
- That side?
- Yes, let's hang in there.

315
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,100
- Right.
- Let's hang in there.

316
00:21:08,700 --> 00:21:09,700
Beautiful.

317
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:16,533
At that construction site yard,
piled high with cement and steel bars,

318
00:21:17,533 --> 00:21:20,533
with dust flying everywhere,

319
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:23,733
you were looking at flowers.

320
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:28,233
Flowers with no names,
blooming through cracks...

321
00:21:29,133 --> 00:21:30,900
in the split cement ground.

322
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:34,400
You smiled so brightly looking at them,

323
00:21:35,700 --> 00:21:39,033
it felt like the whole construction site
had turned into a flower garden.

324
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:41,300
Ever since that day,

325
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:45,300
to me, the construction site
was always like a spring day.

326
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:47,133
Silly.

327
00:21:48,300 --> 00:21:50,533
Knowing how much you love flowers,

328
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:52,633
all those long years,

329
00:21:53,900 --> 00:21:57,600
how did I never think
to take you flower viewing even once?

330
00:21:58,200 --> 00:22:02,333
I never actually wanted
to go flower viewing.

331
00:22:04,700 --> 00:22:07,133
Because all the time I spent living
with you...

332
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:10,100
was like spring to me.

333
00:22:11,233 --> 00:22:12,300
Spring? No way.

334
00:22:14,033 --> 00:22:18,200
I only caused you pain.

335
00:22:20,633 --> 00:22:24,100
There were many painful times.

336
00:22:26,233 --> 00:22:27,833
Still,
I got through all those painful years...

337
00:22:28,633 --> 00:22:30,800
because you were there.

338
00:22:31,900 --> 00:22:34,433
So put down the burden in your heart now.

339
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:41,400
I was truly happy to have met you.

340
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:45,000
Have you never resented me?

341
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,233
Not yet.

342
00:22:51,133 --> 00:22:52,600
Not yet,

343
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:55,400
but are you saying you might from now on?

344
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,433
I'll tell you that next time.

345
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:03,200
Next time? When is the next time?

346
00:23:05,933 --> 00:23:07,333
Next spring.

347
00:23:09,300 --> 00:23:13,033
Next year, when we come
flower viewing together again,

348
00:23:14,300 --> 00:23:17,533
if there's anything to resent,
I'll tell you then.

349
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:24,433
I hope I still have another spring too,
Yeong Hwa.

350
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:32,900
Wait for me.

351
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:34,733
Eun Hyeong and Eun Nim
really have no idea.

352
00:24:34,933 --> 00:24:37,000
This burdock and carrot gimbap
is so delicious.

353
00:24:37,133 --> 00:24:39,300
Not just delicious,
it's full of nutrients too.

354
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:40,800
But what's this?

355
00:24:41,833 --> 00:24:44,700
I'm going to take some gimbap
to Eun Hyeong's place too.

356
00:24:45,533 --> 00:24:46,533
You'll come with me, right?

357
00:24:47,700 --> 00:24:48,700
Sure, why not?

358
00:24:49,100 --> 00:24:51,200
I'll clean up here, so hurry and go.

359
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:52,800
Freshly made gimbap tastes the best.

360
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:54,400
Right, delicious food...

361
00:24:55,133 --> 00:24:56,400
should be delivered while it's warm.

362
00:24:56,633 --> 00:24:57,933
- Let's go.
- We'll be back.

363
00:24:57,933 --> 00:24:58,933
Okay.

364
00:25:07,833 --> 00:25:10,100
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, are you working two jobs?

365
00:25:14,333 --> 00:25:15,833
What do you mean? Two jobs?

366
00:25:16,100 --> 00:25:18,600
I just stepped out for a moment
because I had something to do.

367
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:21,633
Looks like your friends are here.

368
00:25:21,900 --> 00:25:22,900
What did you say?

369
00:25:23,933 --> 00:25:26,800
Are you saying the rabbit in that picture
is me?

370
00:25:27,133 --> 00:25:29,400
Isn't it? It looks like you.

371
00:25:30,500 --> 00:25:31,500
What are you doing right now?

372
00:25:32,133 --> 00:25:33,900
Right now? Eating carrots...

373
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:37,200
What do you need?

374
00:25:37,600 --> 00:25:39,933
I came up with a good idea
for the retirement community concept.

375
00:25:39,933 --> 00:25:41,100
Let's have a meeting tonight.

376
00:25:41,400 --> 00:25:43,100
A meeting? It's my day off today.

377
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:45,600
You made all that fuss
about wanting to work.

378
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:47,400
Come to the office by 6 p.m.

379
00:25:57,700 --> 00:25:59,600
What kind of terrible boss is this?

380
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:01,800
I should report you
to the Ministry of Labor.

381
00:26:08,700 --> 00:26:12,200
Your fever seems too high.
We need a fever reducer first.

382
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:31,100
This won't do.
I'll call an ambulance right away.

383
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:33,400
Don't.

384
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:36,200
Yeong Hwa.

385
00:26:37,500 --> 00:26:38,500
Tonight,

386
00:26:39,733 --> 00:26:42,233
I want to be alone with only you.

387
00:26:43,300 --> 00:26:45,800
No. Something bad could happen.

388
00:26:47,100 --> 00:26:48,600
Maybe we shouldn't have left home.

389
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:51,833
I think
you pushed yourself too hard today.

390
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:53,400
What are you talking about?

391
00:26:54,533 --> 00:26:56,333
Today, I was so...

392
00:26:57,500 --> 00:27:00,000
happy and had so much fun.

393
00:27:01,900 --> 00:27:04,933
I'm sorry, today of all days...

394
00:27:08,133 --> 00:27:11,100
You took fever medicine,
so your fever will go down soon.

395
00:27:11,700 --> 00:27:14,000
As soon as morning comes,
I'll call an ambulance.

396
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:15,800
Yeong Hwa.

397
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:19,600
Yes, tell me.

398
00:27:20,500 --> 00:27:21,833
I will never...

399
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:27,933
leave you alone and go first.

400
00:27:28,300 --> 00:27:29,300
Okay.

401
00:27:30,533 --> 00:27:34,100
Never leave me alone. Never.

402
00:27:38,700 --> 00:27:39,700
Honey.

403
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:43,300
Please wake up. Open your eyes.

404
00:27:44,033 --> 00:27:45,533
Honey, please!

405
00:27:46,533 --> 00:27:47,533
Honey.

406
00:27:48,133 --> 00:27:49,200
Kang Su.

407
00:28:07,900 --> 00:28:10,600
(Our Happy Days)

408
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:12,600
My grandpa is in an ambulance right now.

409
00:28:12,600 --> 00:28:14,433
You should've taken responsibility
to the end.

410
00:28:14,433 --> 00:28:16,000
Last time too, while he was with Gyeol...

411
00:28:16,133 --> 00:28:19,000
What? Is Team Manager
also an ugly duckling like me?

412
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:21,533
Oh My Oz is the crazy girl?

413
00:28:21,533 --> 00:28:22,900
You perverted psycho.

414
00:28:22,900 --> 00:28:25,100
You're forever gone from my life.

415
00:28:25,500 --> 00:28:26,700
This is why you're so clueless.

416
00:28:26,700 --> 00:28:29,100
Team Manager's arrow is pointed at you.

417
00:28:29,100 --> 00:28:30,400
Let's have a talk, Team Manager.

418
00:28:30,400 --> 00:28:31,933
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
